revision.text:
{{Infobox building | name = 277 Fifth | alternate_names = | building_type = | architectural_style = | classification = | location = New York City | address = 277 Fifth Avenue | location_city = | location_country = United States | coordinates = {{coord|40.745661|-73.986275|type:landmark_globe:earth_region:US-NY|display=ti}} | status = Completed | est_completion = 2018 | topped_out_date = | completion_date = | closing_date = | cost = | height = 673 feet | architectural = | tip = | antenna_spire = | material = | size = | floor_area = | floor_count = 55 | architect = [[Rafael Viñoly]] | references = <ref>{{ctbuh|20128}}</ref> }} '''277 Fifth''' (also called '''281 5th Avenue''') is a building under construction in the New York City borough [[Manhattan]] designed by architect [[Rafael Viñoly]]. Plans for the building were first announced in 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newyorkyimby.com/2015/04/51-story-luxury-residential-tower-at-281-fifth-avenue-to-break-ground-by-2016.html|title=51-Story Luxury Residential Tower At 281 Fifth Avenue To Break Ground By 2016|last=Wilson|first=Reid|date=22 April 2015|publisher=YIMBY|accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref> and construction began in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newyorkyimby.com/2016/11/foundation-work-underway-on-52-story-141-unit-mixed-use-tower-at-281-fifth-avenue-nomad.html|title=Foundation Work Underway On 52-Story, 141-Unit Mixed-Use Tower At 281 Fifth Avenue, NoMad|last=Wilson|first=Reid|date=18 November 2016|publisher=YIMBY|accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref> It topped out in March 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://newyorkyimby.com/2018/03/vinoly-designed-277-fifth-avenue-officially-tops-out-at-55-floors-and-663-feet-in-nomad.html|title=Viñoly-Designed 277 Fifth Avenue Officially Tops Out At 55 Floors and 663 Feet in NoMad|last=|first=|date=2018-03-09|work=New York YIMBY|access-date=2018-08-13|language=en-US}}</ref>
Upon completion, the building will have 55 stories and contain 130 residential condominiums.<ref name=curbed1>{{cite web|url=https://ny.curbed.com/2017/7/18/15992434/rafael-vinoly-nomad-manhattan-condo-building-construction|title=Rafael Viñoly’s 55-story Nomad tower is on the rise|last=Walker|first=Ameena|date=18 July 2017|publisher=Curbed|accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref> It has been compared to another building of Viñoly's, [[432 Park Avenue]].<ref name=curbed1/>
==See also== * [[List of tallest buildings in New York City]]
