* '''[[Olney, Buckinghamshire|Olney]]''', [[Buckinghamshire]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɔː|n|i}} (local pronunciation);<ref>[http://www.localauthoritypublishing.co.uk/councils/olney/index.html Olney Town Council Official Guide]</ref> {{IPAc-en|ˈ|oʊ|l|n|i}}<ref name=wells />
* '''[[Osbournby]]''', [[Lincolnshire]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɒ|z|ən|b|i}}
* '''[[Oswaldtwistle]]''', [[Lancashire]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɒ|z|əl|t|w|ɪ|z|əl}}<ref name="h2g2">[http://www.bbc.co.uk/dna/h2g2/A19773499 Pronouncing British Placenames] at BBC's Edited Guide Entry h2g2 site</ref> (local pronunciation);{{citation needed|date=May 2010|reason=Wells's Longman Pronunciation Dictionary gives only an intuitive versions with or without a d sound.}}<ref name=wells /> <!-- I've never heard it pronounced like this. Is there a way of indicating that a reference is dubious? see discuss-->
* '''[[Ovingham]]''', [[Northumberland]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɒ|v|ɪ|n|dʒ|ə|m}} - mirrors nearby Whittingham

